 same amount |\n| 4 | Tier selection is locked once bet is placed | SATISFIED | state.rs:20 CoinflipMatch.tier immutable after creation |\n| 5 | Join requires connected wallet with sufficient balance | SATISFIED | CoinflipContext.tsx:206 joinMatch, chain.ts:241 buildJoinMatchTx |\n\n### FR-3: Flip Resolution\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 1 | Flip begins immediately when both players committed | RESOLVED | MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF callback now active on devnet. join_match CPIs into VRF program which calls back resolve_match. Program redeployed without mock-oracle feature (2026-02-19). |\n| 2 | VRF determines the outcome | RESOLVED | MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF integrated. join_match.rs:88-123 sends VRF request, VRF program calls back resolve_match with randomness. Oracle authority = PDA([\"identity\"], VRF_PROGRAM). |\n| 3 | Result is deterministic and reproducible from VRF seed | PARTIAL | from_randomness(byte) is deterministic. VRF proof exists on-chain via MagicBlock but no UI to display/verify it yet. |\n| 4 | Flip animation plays with coin rotation and landing | SATISFIED | CoinAnimation.tsx:20 CSS 3D transform with spinning-heads/spinning-tails classes, dual faces |\n\n### FR-4: Settlement and Payout\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 1 | Winner payout = total_pool × 0.97 (3% fee) | SATISFIED | claim_payout.rs:55, fees.rs:5 TOTAL_FEE_BPS=300, test coinflip.ts:575 |\n| 2 | Platform fee collected to treasury PDA | SATISFIED | claim_payout.rs treasury transfer, coinflip.ts:575 |\n| 3 | Payout eligibility recorded on-chain | SATISFIED | state.rs winner+claimed fields, claim_payout CPI to update_player_profile |\n| 4 | Winner can claim funds successfully | SATISFIED | claim_payout.rs:55, CoinflipContext.tsx:268, coinflip.ts:575 |\n| 5 | Settlement is idempotent (no double-settle) | SATISFIED | error.rs AlreadyClaimed, coinflip.ts:617 \"rejects double claim\" |\n| 6 | Replay protection for signed actions | SATISFIED | Match closed after claim (rent → creator), Anchor tx signature dedup |\n\n### FR-5: Fairness Verification\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 1 | Completed match displays VRF seed/proof details | DEFERRED | UI fields exist in CoinflipPage but chain.ts:133 sets seedHash=\"\" and no VRF proof populated. Deferred (Scope Decisions: \"fairness verification UI\"). |\n| 2 | Players can independently verify result matches VRF | DEFERRED | VRF integration deferred (Scope Decisions). |\n| 3 | Verification accessible from match history and result screen | DEFERRED | CoinflipPage has /fairness link in history modal but no verification logic. Deferred (Scope Decisions). |\n\n### FR-6: Lobby Browser UI\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 1 | Open games list shows creator name/avatar, tier, amount, side, join button | SATISFIED | MatchCard.tsx:13 (PlayerAvatar:25, getDisplayName:28, tier:50, amount:41, side:36, join:57) |\n| 2 | Filter by tier | SATISFIED | OpenMatchesList.tsx:43 `matches.filter(m => m.tier === selectedTier)` |\n| 3 | Sort by newest/oldest/amount | SATISFIED | OpenMatchesList.tsx:18 sortMatches, :79 select dropdown |\n| 4 | Create Game panel with tier selection grid and Heads/Tails toggle | SATISFIED | CoinflipPage.tsx sidebar: TierSelector + CoinSideSelector.tsx:19 |\n| 5 | Estimated wait time (deferred if data unavailable) | DEFERRED | Self-deferred in criterion text (\"deferred to post-MVP polish if data unavailable\"). Not implemented. |\n\n### FR-7: Active Game and Result UI\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 1 | Both players shown with avatars, names, wager amounts | SATISFIED | ActiveMatchView.tsx:88-108 PlayerAvatarCompact, side labels, entry amount |\n| 2 | 3D coin flip animation with multiple rotations and gradual slowdown | SATISFIED | CoinAnimation.tsx:20 CSS 3D transform (front/back faces :53-58), spinning classes :43-45 |\n| 3 | Winning side highlighted with glow effect | SATISFIED | ActiveMatchView.tsx:200-205 result color + textShadow glow |\n| 4 | \"YOU WIN!\" or \"YOU LOSE\" overlay displayed | SATISFIED | ActiveMatchView.tsx:128 \"You Won!\", :129-139 \"You Lost\" with heart+shards animation |\n| 5 | Payout amount shown for winner | SATISFIED | ActiveMatchView.tsx:207-210 `match.payoutAmount.toFixed(4) SOL` |\n| 6 | Quick rematch option available after result | GAP | Not implemented in ActiveMatchView.tsx. No rematch button or flow exists. |\n\n### FR-8: Audio Feedback\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 1 | Coin flip spinning sound during animation | DEFERRED | Scope Decisions: \"Deferred to later spec: Audio integration...\" |\n| 2 | Dramatic pause before landing | DEFERRED | Same reference. |\n| 3 | Victory sound for winner | DEFERRED | Same reference. |\n| 4 | Coin clink on landing | DEFERRED | Same reference. |\n\n## Gap Summary\n\n| # | FR | Criterion | Severity | Category | Blocked By | Next Step |\n|---|-----|-----------|----------|----------|------------|-----------|\n| ~~1~~ | ~~FR-3~~ | ~~Flip begins immediately when both committed~~ | ~~critical~~ | ~~backend~~ | ~~Oracle service needed~~ | **RESOLVED** (2026-02-19): MagicBlock VRF callback active, program redeployed without mock-oracle, timeout_cancel safety net added |\n| 2 | FR-7 | Quick rematch option after result | low | frontend | — | Add rematch button to ActiveMatchView complete phase |\n\n## Resolved Items (2026-02-19)\n\n| Item | Resolution |\n|------|-----------|\n| VRF oracle/resolver (FR-3.1) | MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF callback active on devnet. join_match CPIs into VRF program; VRF calls back resolve_match with randomness. Program deployed without mock-oracle feature. |\n| VRF determines outcome (FR-3.2) | MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF integrated and active. |\n| Timeout safety net | New `timeout_cancel` instruction: either player can cancel a LOCKED match after 2 min timeout. Refunds both players. New `lockedAt` field on CoinflipMatch tracks lock time. Frontend shows \"Cancel & Refund\" button after timeout. |\n\n## Deferred Items\n\n| Item | Deferred To | Target Spec | Target Status | Stale? |\n|------|-------------|-------------|---------------|--------|\n| VRF reproducibility (FR-3.3) | later spec | none specified | — | UNTRACKED |\n| VRF seed/proof display (FR-5.1) | later spec | none specified | — | UNTRACKED |\n| Independent verification (FR-5.2) | later spec | none specified | — | UNTRACKED |\n| Verification accessibility (FR-5.3) | later spec | none specified | — | UNTRACKED |\n| Estimated wait time (FR-6.5) | post-MVP polish | none specified | — | UNTRACKED |\n| Spinning sound (FR-8.1) | later spec | none specified | — | UNTRACKED |\n| Dramatic pause sound (FR-8.2) | later spec | none specified | — | UNTRACKED |\n| Victory sound (FR-8.3) | later spec | none specified | — | UNTRACKED |\n| Coin clink sound (FR-8.4) | later spec | none specified | — | UNTRACKED |\n\nAll 10 deferred items are **UNTRACKED** — none reference a specific target spec. All other specs (002-crash through 105-tug-of-earn) remain in Draft status.\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. ~~**Critical gap — Oracle/resolver service**~~: **RESOLVED** (2026-02-19). MagicBlock VRF callback is now active. Program deployed without mock-oracle. Timeout cancel safety net added.\n\n2. **Fairness verification UI spec**: FR-3.3 and all of FR-5 remain deferred. A \"Fairness Verification\" spec would add VRF proof display and independent verification UI. Lower priority now that VRF is live.\n\n3. **Audio spec**: All 4 FR-8 items should be bundled into a dedicated audio/SFX spec covering sound design across all games (coinflip + crash). Low priority for launch.\n\n4. **Quick rematch (FR-7.6)**: Low severity. Could be added to a \"UX Polish\" spec or tacked onto whatever spec addresses the post-resolution flow.\n\n5. **Estimated wait time (FR-6.5)**: Self-deferred and low priority. Requires match fill-rate analytics data that doesn't exist yet. Safe to keep deferred past launch.\n\n6. **Frontend test coverage**: Zero vitest/component tests and zero Playwright E2E tests exist. Not an FR criterion but notable for launch readiness. The spec's Scope Decisions explicitly defer Playwright integration tests.\n","numLines":207,"startLine":1,"totalLines":207}}}
