{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_015FeYugEm9QyZR6RZLGpc4d","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018Y2rgEPjC5Krtx6QhEWt5Z","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/001-coinflip/spec.md","old_string":"- [ ] [docs] Update spec artifacts — refresh `gap-analysis.md`: replace all MagicBlock VRF / `resolve_match` references with Orao / 3-tx-flow architecture, update test counts to current (26 coinflip + 5 platform bankrun tests), mark resolved gaps. Mark resolved carry-forward items in `checklist.md`. Update `history.md` with Phase 2 refinement entry.","new_string":"- [x] [docs] Update spec artifacts — refresh `gap-analysis.md`: replace all MagicBlock VRF / `resolve_match` references with Orao / 3-tx-flow architecture, update test counts to current (26 coinflip + 5 platform bankrun tests), mark resolved gaps. Mark resolved carry-forward items in `checklist.md`. Update `history.md` with Phase 2 refinement entry. (done: iteration 21)"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1090,"cache_read_input_tokens":73306,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1090},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a3554eb9-5d3e-4470-b8e4-3c2e723bd989","uuid":"49f6a2b7-4fa0-4d43-91b7-85aafc7a9580"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018Y2rgEPjC5Krtx6QhEWt5Z","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/001-coinflip/spec.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a3554eb9-5d3e-4470-b8e4-3c2e723bd989","uuid":"6a5ae1fe-00fb-4612-b04a-f5c99ba25bf7","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/001-coinflip/spec.md","oldString":"- [ ] [docs] Update spec artifacts — refresh `gap-analysis.md`: replace all MagicBlock VRF / `resolve_match` references with Orao / 3-tx-flow architecture, update test counts to current (26 coinflip + 5 platform bankrun tests), mark resolved gaps. Mark resolved carry-forward items in `checklist.md`. Update `history.md` with Phase 2 refinement entry.","newString":"- [x] [docs] Update spec artifacts — refresh `gap-analysis.md`: replace all MagicBlock VRF / `resolve_match` references with Orao / 3-tx-flow architecture, update test counts to current (26 coinflip + 5 platform bankrun tests), mark resolved gaps. Mark resolved carry-forward items in `checklist.md`. Update `history.md` with Phase 2 refinement entry. (done: iteration 21)","originalFile":"# Specification: 001 Coinflip\n\n## Meta\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Status | Ready |\n| Ideation | Complete |\n| Priority | P0 |\n| Phase | 1 |\n| NR_OF_TRIES | 20 |\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nCoinflip is the simplest game on the platform and the first end-to-end delivery target. Two players wager equal amounts in a 1v1 match. A verifiable random function determines one winner who takes the entire pot minus the platform fee. It validates the full wager-to-settlement flow before Crash development begins.\n\n## User Stories\n\n- As a player, I want to create a coinflip match by choosing a tier and side so that I can challenge an opponent at stakes I'm comfortable with.\n- As a player, I want to browse open coinflip lobbies so that I can join a match quickly.\n- As a player, I want to see a fair coin flip animation and result so that I trust the outcome is legitimate.\n- As a winner, I want my payout settled on-chain so that I can claim my winnings trustlessly.\n- As a player, I want to verify the fairness of any completed match so that I can confirm the result was not manipulated.\n\n---\n\n## Scope Alignment\n\n- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 (Product Scope - V1 In Scope: Coinflip), Section 5 (V1 Game Scope - Coinflip), Section 8 (Delivery Plan - Phase 1)\n- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n- **Phase boundary**: Phase 1 - Coinflip End-to-End\n\n## Required Context Files\n\n- `sources/rng-utopia/docs/COINFLIP.md` (game concept source)\n- `sources/rng-utopia/docs/PLATFORM.md` (tier-based betting, platform fee, provably fair system)\n- `docs/SCOPE.md` (scope boundary and shared game requirements)\n\n## Contract Files\n\n### Frontend (Existing UI — preserve design/UX)\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` — game state management\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/components/` — ActiveMatchView, CoinAnimation, CoinSideSelector, MatchCard, OpenMatchesList\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts` — frontend type definitions\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/mock-simulation.ts` — mock to be replaced with real chain calls\n\n### Game Engine (TS instruction builders)\n- `packages/game-engine/src/coinflip.ts` — PDA derivation, instruction builders, payout calc\n- `packages/game-engine/src/types.ts` — shared types + fee constants\n- `packages/game-engine/src/payouts.ts` — payout math\n\n### On-Chain (Anchor programs — current implementation)\n- `solana/programs/coinflip/` — Coinflip program (VRF rewrite pending — will use shared crate + Orao per 004 spec)\n- `solana/programs/platform/` — Platform program (player profiles, fee config)\n- `solana/shared/` — Shared Rust lib (fees, tiers, constants — expanding per 004 spec)\n\n---\n\n## Functional Requirements\n\n### FR-1: Match Creation\n\nA player can create a new coinflip match by selecting a betting tier (Iron through Diamond) and a side (Heads or Tails). The match appears in the open games list for other players to join.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] Player can select one of six tiers (Iron 0.005, Bronze 0.01, Silver 0.1, Gold 0.25, Platinum 0.5, Diamond 1 SOL) <!-- satisfied: shared/src/tiers.rs:5 TIER_AMOUNTS, types.ts:25 TIER_AMOUNTS_LAMPORTS, CoinflipPage TierSelector -->\n- [x] Player can choose Heads or Tails <!-- satisfied: shared/src/constants.rs:2-3 SIDE_HEADS/TAILS, CoinSideSelector.tsx:19 -->\n- [x] Created match appears in the lobby browser with creator name, tier, wager amount, and side chosen <!-- satisfied: MatchCard.tsx:13 (PlayerAvatar, tier, amount, side), chain.ts:139 fetchAllOpenMatches -->\n- [x] Match creation requires a connected wallet with sufficient balance <!-- satisfied: CoinflipContext.tsx:169 createMatch, error.rs:19 InsufficientFunds -->\n- [x] Only one active match per player at a time (enforced on-chain via PDA constraint) <!-- satisfied: state.rs:20 CoinflipMatch seeds [\"match\", creator], Anchor init constraint -->\n\n### FR-2: Match Joining\n\nA second player can join an open match. The joiner is automatically assigned the opposite side. Both players must wager the same tier amount.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] Player can browse open matches filtered by tier and sorted by newest/oldest <!-- satisfied: OpenMatchesList.tsx:43 tier filter, :18 sortMatches (newest/oldest/amount) -->\n- [x] Joining assigns the opposite side automatically <!-- satisfied: join_match.rs:25, chain.ts:122-123 onChainMatchToUI -->\n- [x] Both players' wagers are equal (tier-enforced) <!-- satisfied: create_match.rs:28 entry_amount from tier, join_match.rs:25 same amount -->\n- [x] Tier selection is locked once the bet is placed <!-- satisfied: state.rs:20 CoinflipMatch.tier immutable after creation -->\n- [x] Join requires connected wallet with sufficient balance <!-- satisfied: CoinflipContext.tsx:206 joinMatch, chain.ts:241 buildJoinMatchTx -->\n\n### FR-3: Flip Resolution\n\nOnce both players have joined, a coin flip occurs using VRF. The flip animation plays for approximately 3 seconds, then the result is revealed.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] Flip begins immediately when both players are committed <!-- satisfied: join_match.rs embeds Orao VRF request CPI, frontend polls until randomness fulfilled (spec 004 rewrite) -->\n- [x] VRF determines the outcome (Heads or Tails) <!-- satisfied: Orao VRF integrated via shared vrf_orao module, claim_payout reads randomness + derives winner (spec 004 rewrite) -->\n- [x] Result is deterministic and reproducible from the VRF seed <!-- satisfied: from_randomness(byte) is pure deterministic; Orao randomness account persists on-chain for proof; verification UI planned (Phase 2) -->\n- [x] Flip animation plays with coin rotation and landing <!-- satisfied: CoinAnimation.tsx:20 CSS 3D transform, spinning-heads/spinning-tails classes -->\n\n### FR-4: Settlement and Payout\n\nThe winner receives the total pool minus the platform fee. Settlement is recorded on-chain. Either player (winner or loser) can trigger settlement to close the match.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] Winner payout = total_pool x 0.97 (3% platform fee) <!-- satisfied: claim_payout.rs:55, fees.rs:5 TOTAL_FEE_BPS=300, test coinflip.ts:575 -->\n- [x] Platform fee is collected to treasury PDA <!-- satisfied: claim_payout.rs treasury transfer, test coinflip.ts:575 -->\n- [x] Payout eligibility is recorded on-chain <!-- satisfied: state.rs winner+claimed fields, claim_payout CPI to update_player_profile -->\n- [x] Winner can claim funds successfully <!-- satisfied: claim_payout.rs:55, CoinflipContext.tsx:268, test coinflip.ts:575 -->\n- [x] Either player can trigger settlement (loser is not blocked) <!-- satisfied: claim_payout.rs caller validated as creator OR opponent, payout always goes to winner -->\n- [x] Settlement is idempotent (cannot double-settle) <!-- satisfied: error.rs AlreadyClaimed, test coinflip.ts:617 \"rejects double claim\" -->\n- [x] Replay protection for signed actions <!-- satisfied: match account closed after claim, Anchor tx signature dedup -->\n\n### FR-4b: Cancellation and Refunds\n\nAll cancellations refund deposited amounts in full. No platform fee is kept on cancellation.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] Creator can cancel a match in WAITING phase (before opponent joins) <!-- satisfied: cancel_match.rs, phase==WAITING check -->\n- [x] Cancel refunds full entry amount + rent to creator <!-- satisfied: cancel_match.rs close=creator, all lamports returned -->\n- [x] Timeout cancel refunds both players if VRF does not resolve within 2 minutes <!-- satisfied: timeout_cancel.rs, entry_amount refunded to each player -->\n- [x] No platform fee is deducted on any cancellation <!-- satisfied: cancel_match.rs and timeout_cancel.rs have no fee calculation -->\n- [x] Either player can trigger timeout cancel <!-- satisfied: timeout_cancel.rs caller == creator OR opponent -->\n\n### FR-5: Fairness Verification\n\nPlayers can verify the outcome of any completed match by inspecting the VRF inputs and recalculating the result.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Completed match displays VRF seed/proof details <!-- planned: MatchSettled event includes randomness bytes; Phase 2 adds vrf_request_key to event, verification UI reads Orao account -->\n- [ ] Players can independently verify the result matches the VRF output <!-- planned: Phase 2 verification.ts re-derives result from Orao randomness bytes via from_randomness -->\n- [ ] Verification is accessible from match history and result screen <!-- planned: Phase 2 verification UI accessible from ActiveMatchView + /fairness link -->\n\n### FR-6: Lobby Browser UI\n\nA browsable list of open coinflip matches with filtering and creation controls.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] Open games list shows creator name/avatar, tier, wager amount, side, and join button <!-- satisfied: MatchCard.tsx:13 (PlayerAvatar:25, tier:50, amount:41, side:36, join:57) -->\n- [x] Filter by tier <!-- satisfied: OpenMatchesList.tsx:43 matches.filter(m => m.tier === selectedTier) -->\n- [x] Sort by newest/oldest/amount <!-- satisfied: OpenMatchesList.tsx:18 sortMatches, :79 sort dropdown -->\n- [x] Create Game panel with tier selection grid and Heads/Tails toggle <!-- satisfied: CoinflipPage.tsx sidebar TierSelector + CoinSideSelector.tsx:19 -->\n- [ ] Estimated wait time shown (derived from recent match fill rate — deferred to post-MVP polish if data unavailable) <!-- deferred: self-deferred in criterion text, no match fill-rate data available -->\n\n### FR-7: Active Game and Result UI\n\nThe in-match view showing both players, coin flip animation, and result.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] Both players shown with avatars, names, and wager amounts <!-- satisfied: ActiveMatchView.tsx:88-108 PlayerAvatarCompact, side labels, entry amount -->\n- [x] 3D coin flip animation with multiple rotations and gradual slowdown <!-- satisfied: CoinAnimation.tsx:20 CSS 3D transform (front/back faces :53-58), spinning classes :43-45 -->\n- [x] Winning side highlighted with glow effect <!-- satisfied: ActiveMatchView.tsx:200-205 result color + textShadow glow -->\n- [x] \"YOU WIN!\" or \"YOU LOSE\" overlay displayed <!-- satisfied: ActiveMatchView.tsx:128 \"You Won!\", :129-139 \"You Lost\" with heart+shards animation -->\n- [x] Payout amount shown for winner <!-- satisfied: ActiveMatchView.tsx:207-210 match.payoutAmount.toFixed(4) SOL -->\n- [ ] Quick rematch option available after result <!-- planned: Phase 2 rematch button in ActiveMatchView, reuses createMatch with same tier/side -->\n\n### FR-8: Audio Feedback\n\nSound effects accompany the coinflip experience.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Coin flip spinning sound during animation <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred (Scope Decisions) -->\n- [ ] Dramatic pause before landing <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred (Scope Decisions) -->\n- [ ] Victory sound for winner <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred (Scope Decisions) -->\n- [ ] Coin clink on landing <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred (Scope Decisions) -->\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- A player can create a match, have it joined, see the flip, and receive payout in a single uninterrupted flow\n- Settlement correctness: winner always receives exactly (pool x 0.97), fee always reaches treasury\n- Any completed match can be independently verified for fairness\n- Match creation to resolution completes within 10 seconds of both players joining\n- Error states (insufficient balance, network failure, wallet disconnect) are clearly communicated\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Wallet connection via `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` (Privy removed)\n- Coinflip Anchor program (`solana/programs/coinflip`) with VRF provider (Orao, per `004-shared-infrastructure` spec)\n- Platform Anchor program (`solana/programs/platform`) for player profiles + fee config\n- `packages/anchor-client/` (generated from IDL via `scripts/sync-idl`)\n- Shared UI components (`packages/ui/`) for buttons, modals, cards, toasts\n- Dev environment: Anchor CLI 0.32.1, Solana CLI 2.3.13, Rust toolchain\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- Tier amounts are fixed at the values defined in PLATFORM.md\n- Platform fee is 3% (300 bps). Confirmed in `docs/FOUNDATIONS.md` §8. Split: 200 bps revenue, 70 bps rakeback, 30 bps chest treasury.\n- VRF provider: Orao (per `docs/specs/004-shared-infrastructure/spec.md` FR-4). MagicBlock VRF dropped.\n- Non-custodial wallet flow via `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` (no Privy, no internal balance model)\n- Existing on-chain programs are legacy — coinflip will be rewritten against new shared crate + chosen VRF provider (see `004-shared-infrastructure` spec)\n\n---\n\n## Validation Plan\n\n| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| 1 | Match creation with tier + side | Create match via UI, verify lobby listing | Screenshot of lobby with new match |\n| 2 | Match joining assigns opposite side | Join match, verify side assignment | Screenshot showing both players |\n| 3 | VRF determines outcome | Inspect VRF output, verify determinism | VRF proof + recalculated result |\n| 4 | Winner payout = pool x 0.97 | Check on-chain settlement transaction | Explorer link showing amounts |\n| 5 | Platform fee reaches treasury | Check treasury PDA balance | Explorer link showing fee transfer |\n| 6 | Settlement is idempotent | Attempt double-settle, verify rejection | Error response or no-op proof |\n| 7 | Fairness verification works | Use verification UI to recalculate result | Screenshot of verification view |\n| 8 | End-to-end flow completes | Full playthrough from create to claim | Video or step-by-step screenshots |\n\n---\n\n## Completion Signal\n\n### Implementation Checklist\n\n**Phase 1: Core Implementation (complete)**\n- [x] [on-chain] CoinflipConfig PDA + initialize_config instruction (done: TDD stubs commit)\n- [x] [on-chain] CoinflipMatch state + create_match instruction with tier validation + escrow (done: TDD stubs commit)\n- [x] [on-chain] Align shared crate tiers with spec: 6 tiers Iron→Diamond, amounts match 0.005→1.0 SOL (done: iteration 1)\n- [x] [on-chain] Implement join_match — phase check, opponent != creator, escrow transfer, set LOCKED (done: iteration 2)\n- [x] [on-chain] Implement resolve_match — oracle authority check, randomness→winner derivation (done: iteration 3; NOTE: deleted in 004 rewrite, replaced by claim-time VRF read)\n- [x] [on-chain] Implement claim_payout — settlement, fee transfer, profile CPI, either-player trigger (done: iteration 4)\n- [x] [on-chain] Implement cancel_match — WAITING-only, full refund + close (done: iteration 5)\n- [x] [on-chain] Platform program scaffold — PlatformConfig + PlayerProfile + instructions (done: iteration 6)\n- [x] [on-chain] CPI from coinflip claim_payout → platform update_player_profile (done: iteration 7)\n- [x] [engine] Create anchor-client package + sync-idl script (done: iteration 1, engine phase)\n- [x] [engine] Align game-engine with on-chain — types.ts side values, coinflip.ts PDA rewrite (done: iteration 7)\n- [x] [frontend] Wire CoinflipContext to anchor-client — delete mock-simulation.ts, real chain calls (done: iteration 8)\n- [x] [frontend] Wire lobby browser + error handling (done: iteration 9)\n\n**Phase 1b: Shared Infrastructure Rewrite (complete — spec 004)**\n- [x] [on-chain] Orao VRF integration — join_match embeds VRF request, claim_payout reads randomness at claim time (done: spec 004)\n- [x] [on-chain] resolve_match deleted — 3-tx flow: create→join(+VRF)→claim(+settle) (done: spec 004)\n- [x] [on-chain] Shared crate modules: lifecycle, timeout, escrow, fees, pause, vrf_orao, commit_reveal, cpi (done: spec 004)\n- [x] [on-chain] timeout_cancel + force_close instructions (done: spec 004)\n- [x] [engine] IDL re-synced for rewritten programs (done: spec 004)\n- [x] [frontend] chain.ts rewritten for Orao VRF account structures (done: spec 004)\n\n**Phase 2: Data Consistency**\n- [x] [engine] Fix tier naming and amounts — in `packages/game-engine/src/types.ts`: rename `Tier` union member `\"emerald\"` → `\"platinum\"`, update `TIER_AMOUNTS` values to SOL `{iron: 0.005, bronze: 0.01, silver: 0.1, gold: 0.25, platinum: 0.5, diamond: 1.0}`. Propagate `\"emerald\"` → `\"platinum\"` rename to ALL consumers across the monorepo (16 files reference \"emerald\" — use typecheck errors to find them all: `chain.ts`, `index.css`, boss-raid, lord-of-rngs, game-of-trades, crypto-crash, player-profile features). Verify: `pnpm lint` + `pnpm typecheck` pass across all packages. (done: iteration 10)\n- [x] [frontend] Verify tier display correctness after amounts fix — confirm CoinflipPage TierSelector shows SOL values `{0.005, 0.01, 0.1, 0.25, 0.5, 1.0}`, MatchCard displays correct wager amounts, `chain.ts` `entryAmountSol` reads correct values. Fix any hardcoded tier amount references that don't flow from `TIER_AMOUNTS`. Verify: `pnpm build` succeeds for platform app. (done: iteration 11)\n\n**Phase 2: Claimable Matches (G-1)**\n- [x] [frontend] Add `fetchClaimableMatches(connection, playerPubkey)` to `features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` — use `getProgramAccounts` with memcmp filters for matches where player is `creator` OR `opponent`, `claimed == false`, phase is non-terminal. Must handle both cases (player as creator and player as opponent are separate queries since the pubkey is at different offsets). Return `UIMatch[]`. Verify: `pnpm typecheck` passes. (done: iteration 12)\n- [x] [frontend] Surface claimable matches in CoinflipContext + CoinflipPage — add `claimableMatches: UIMatch[]` to context state, poll via `fetchClaimableMatches` alongside open matches. Show \"Your Matches\" section in CoinflipPage above the open lobby list with claim/cancel actions per match. Verify: `pnpm build` succeeds. (done: iteration 13)\n\n**Phase 2: Fairness Verification (FR-5)**\n- [x] [on-chain] Add `vrf_request_key: Pubkey` field to `MatchSettled` event — in `solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs` (event definition) and `claim_payout.rs` (emit site), add `vrf_request_key` from `coinflip_match.vrf_request_key`. This enables verification UIs to look up the Orao randomness account and confirm the randomness bytes are genuine VRF output. Verify: `anchor build -p coinflip` succeeds + all bankrun tests pass. (done: iteration 14)\n- [x] [engine] Re-sync IDL after MatchSettled event change — run `./scripts/sync-idl` to copy updated IDL + types into `packages/anchor-client/`. Verify anchor-client exports include `vrf_request_key` in MatchSettled event type. Verify: `pnpm typecheck` passes across monorepo. (done: iteration 15)\n- [x] [frontend] Build fairness verification utility — create `features/coinflip/utils/verification.ts`. Export `verifyMatch(connection, claimTxSignature): Promise<VerificationResult>`. Logic: (1) fetch parsed transaction by signature, (2) extract `MatchSettled` event from logs (parse program event data), (3) read `randomness` bytes from event, (4) re-derive result via `from_randomness(randomness[0])`, (5) compare derived winner to event `winner` field, (6) fetch Orao randomness account by `vrf_request_key` to confirm VRF fulfillment. Return `{verified, creator, opponent, winner, randomnessHex, derivedResult, vrfFulfilled}`. Verify: `pnpm typecheck` passes. (done: iteration 16)\n- [x] [frontend] Build fairness verification UI — add \"Verify Fairness\" button to ActiveMatchView (visible in completed phase). Opens a verification panel/modal showing: claim tx signature, VRF request key, raw randomness hex, derived result (Heads/Tails), recorded winner, verification status badge (Verified/Failed/Pending). Also wire the existing `/fairness` link in CoinflipPage to use this verification flow (user pastes a tx signature to verify any match). Verify: `pnpm build` succeeds. (done: iteration 17)\n\n**Phase 2: Quick Rematch (FR-7.6)**\n- [x] [frontend] Add rematch button to ActiveMatchView — visible when match phase is `complete`. Clicking calls `createMatch` with the same tier and the player's original side choice. Creates a new open match in the lobby — the opponent must find and join it manually (no forced rematch). Button text: \"Play Again\". Reuses the existing `createMatch` context action. Verify: `pnpm build` succeeds. (done: iteration 18)\n\n**Phase 2: Validation & Cleanup**\n- [x] [test] Validate carry-forward invariants against post-004 code — read and verify: (a) `vrf_request_key` is stored on `CoinflipMatch` state and now emitted in `MatchSettled` event, (b) `from_randomness()` in `shared/src/constants.rs` is pure deterministic (same byte → same side, every time), (c) `timeout_cancel` uses `shared::timeout::is_expired()` + `shared::vrf_orao::is_fulfilled()` guard, (d) `join_match` rejects non-WAITING phase, `claim_payout` rejects `claimed==true` (idempotency), (e) `create_match` calls `shared::pause::check_not_paused()`, VRF unfulfilled → claim rejects. Log each finding with file:line evidence in `docs/specs/001-coinflip/history.md`. Verify: all bankrun tests pass. (done: iteration 19)\n- [x] [frontend] Remove dead code — delete unused `buildCreateMatchInstruction` export from `chain.ts` (only `buildCreateMatchTx` is used). Remove stale \"Simplified match type for UI/mock mode\" comment from `types.ts`. Verify: `pnpm lint` + `pnpm typecheck` pass. (done: iteration 20)\n- [ ] [docs] Update spec artifacts — refresh `gap-analysis.md`: replace all MagicBlock VRF / `resolve_match` references with Orao / 3-tx-flow architecture, update test counts to current (26 coinflip + 5 platform bankrun tests), mark resolved gaps. Mark resolved carry-forward items in `checklist.md`. Update `history.md` with Phase 2 refinement entry.\n- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for coinflip pages. Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures from tier name/amount changes. Then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate:\n  - **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent, only expected areas changed) → commit updated baselines\n  - **REVIEW** (changes look plausible but unexpected areas also changed, or uncertain) → do NOT commit baselines. Save the diff images from `test-results/` to `docs/specs/001-coinflip/visual-review/`, describe concerns in `history.md`, output `<blocker>Visual review needed: [describe what looks off]</blocker>`\n  - **FAIL** (layout broken, elements missing, clearly wrong) → fix the code, do NOT update baselines\n\n### Scope Decisions\n\n- **Tiers**: On-chain canonical (Iron→Diamond, 0.005→1.0 SOL). Game-engine types.ts to be aligned (Phase 2 item). Rename \"emerald\" → \"platinum\" platform-wide.\n- **Side discriminants**: 0/1 canonical (heads=0, tails=1).\n- **VRF**: Orao integration complete (spec 004). Mock-vrf feature for bankrun tests. 3-tx flow: create→join(+VRF request)→claim(+VRF read+settle).\n- **Platform program**: Included with CPI for player profile updates on settlement.\n- **Fairness verification**: Event-based approach — MatchSettled event (with randomness + vrf_request_key) + Orao randomness account lookup. No match PDA persistence needed.\n- **Deferred**: Audio integration (all 4 FR-8 items → dedicated audio spec), estimated wait time (FR-6.5 → requires match fill-rate analytics infrastructure).\n\n### Iteration Instructions\n\nEach checklist item is one autonomous iteration (`claude -p` invocation). The agent:\n1. Reads this spec + history.md for prior context\n2. Implements the next unchecked item\n3. Runs the verification command specified in the item\n4. If verification passes → checks the box, commits, outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n5. If verification fails → outputs `<blocker>description</blocker>` and exits\n\n**Only when ALL items are checked, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":251,"oldLines":7,"newStart":251,"newLines":7,"lines":[" **Phase 2: Validation & Cleanup**"," - [x] [test] Validate carry-forward invariants against post-004 code — read and verify: (a) `vrf_request_key` is stored on `CoinflipMatch` state and now emitted in `MatchSettled` event, (b) `from_randomness()` in `shared/src/constants.rs` is pure deterministic (same byte → same side, every time), (c) `timeout_cancel` uses `shared::timeout::is_expired()` + `shared::vrf_orao::is_fulfilled()` guard, (d) `join_match` rejects non-WAITING phase, `claim_payout` rejects `claimed==true` (idempotency), (e) `create_match` calls `shared::pause::check_not_paused()`, VRF unfulfilled → claim rejects. Log each finding with file:line evidence in `docs/specs/001-coinflip/history.md`. Verify: all bankrun tests pass. (done: iteration 19)"," - [x] [frontend] Remove dead code — delete unused `buildCreateMatchInstruction` export from `chain.ts` (only `buildCreateMatchTx` is used). Remove stale \"Simplified match type for UI/mock mode\" comment from `types.ts`. Verify: `pnpm lint` + `pnpm typecheck` pass. (done: iteration 20)","-- [ ] [docs] Update spec artifacts — refresh `gap-analysis.md`: replace all MagicBlock VRF / `resolve_match` references with Orao / 3-tx-flow architecture, update test counts to current (26 coinflip + 5 platform bankrun tests), mark resolved gaps. Mark resolved carry-forward items in `checklist.md`. Update `history.md` with Phase 2 refinement entry.","+- [x] [docs] Update spec artifacts — refresh `gap-analysis.md`: replace all MagicBlock VRF / `resolve_match` references with Orao / 3-tx-flow architecture, update test counts to current (26 coinflip + 5 platform bankrun tests), mark resolved gaps. Mark resolved carry-forward items in `checklist.md`. Update `history.md` with Phase 2 refinement entry. (done: iteration 21)"," - [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for coinflip pages. Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures from tier name/amount changes. Then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate:","   - **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent, only expected areas changed) → commit updated baselines","   - **REVIEW** (changes look plausible but unexpected areas also changed, or uncertain) → do NOT commit baselines. Save the diff images from `test-results/` to `docs/specs/001-coinflip/visual-review/`, describe concerns in `history.md`, output `<blocker>Visual review needed: [describe what looks off]</blocker>`"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
